PermissibleValues.value: A23  New Recruitment Strategy Started (specify in Study Event Type Description)
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A23  New Recruitment Strategy Started (specify in Study Event Type Description)

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A23  New Recruitment Strategy Started (specify in Study Event Type Description)
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: New recruitment strategy added at a site, updates to recruitment materials, could be Site issue or study wide.

PermissibleValues.value: A0  Change in Monthly Accrual (provide new monthly accrual rate in Study Event Description)
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A0  Change in Monthly Accrual (provide new monthly accrual rate in Study Event Description)

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A0  Change in Monthly Accrual (provide new monthly accrual rate in Study Event Description)
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Projected Accrual Rate Change

PermissibleValues.value: A19  Staff Issues: LAO Staff Turnover/ Availability
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A19  Staff Issues: LAO Staff Turnover/ Availability

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A19  Staff Issues: LAO Staff Turnover/ Availability
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Refers to coordinator turnover or Issues that interfere with LAO staff s availability, and resources, such as monitoring visits, staff vacations, multiple studies.

PermissibleValues.value: A28  Other (specify in Study Event Type Description)
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A28  Other (specify in Study Event Type Description)

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A28  Other (specify in Study Event Type Description)
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Other reason not specified in the dropdown list.

PermissibleValues.value: A3  Site Open (Provide Date in Study Event Type Description)
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A3  Site Open (Provide Date in Study Event Type Description)

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A3  Site Open (Provide Date in Study Event Type Description)
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Date site made first person-to-person, live contact with a participant for this study (phone, in-person or online). Each site must supply date of contact with first patient. This is the start date for the AQuIP Zone Monitor Reports (ZMR). Zones are calculated based on the date that the FIRST SITE makes first contact with the first participant.

PermissibleValues.value: A9  Accrual Hold; specify in Study Event Description
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A9  Accrual Hold; specify in Study Event Description

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A9  Accrual Hold; specify in Study Event Description
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Accrual on hold for reason other than FDA clinical hold, protocol-defined hold, or any site-specific reason.  Specify in Event Description. Accrual Holds should be reported on the Protocol Status Update Form.

PermissibleValues.value: A29  Amendment Activated at Accrual Site
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A29  Amendment Activated at Accrual Site

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A29  Amendment Activated at Accrual Site
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Date the amendment was approved at the accrual site Intended to capture when relevant amendments are approved for implementation at each accrual site as this may be substantially later than CIRB approval.

PermissibleValues.value: A27  Local Event Type: Hospital/ Educational Event Type
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A27  Local Event Type: Hospital/ Educational Event Type

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A27  Local Event Type: Hospital/ Educational Event Type
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Hospital or institutional educational event promoting clinical trials.

PermissibleValues.value: A26  Time of Year: Weather
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A26  Time of Year: Weather

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A26  Time of Year: Weather
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Site closure or reduced operational hours or other issues related to weather, e.g. snowstorms, hurricanes, severe weather.

PermissibleValues.value: A24  Time of Year: National/Religious Holiday
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A24  Time of Year: National/Religious Holiday

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A24  Time of Year: National/Religious Holiday
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Site closure due to holiday.

PermissibleValues.value: A22  Staff Issues: Site Staff Workload
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A22  Staff Issues: Site Staff Workload

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A22  Staff Issues: Site Staff Workload
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Events or issues such as monitoring visits, multiple studies, but not refer to competing study.

PermissibleValues.value: A21  Staff Issues: Site Staff Turnover/ Availability
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A21  Staff Issues: Site Staff Turnover/ Availability

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A21  Staff Issues: Site Staff Turnover/ Availability
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Refers to site coordinator turnover or Issues that interfere with coordinators availability and resources, such as monitoring visits, multiple studies, out of office due to vacation, maternity/paternity leave, family emergency, etc.

PermissibleValues.value: A18  PI Issues: Availability
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A18  PI Issues: Availability

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A18  PI Issues: Availability
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: PI out of office or otherwise unavailable.

PermissibleValues.value: A17a - CIRB Protocol Amendment Approval: Site Removal
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A17a - CIRB Protocol Amendment Approval: Site Removal

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A17a - CIRB Protocol Amendment Approval: Site Removal
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Protocol amendment approval by CIRB for site removal.   (Amendments for removals are often delayed until it can be coupled with the next substantial amendment ).

PermissibleValues.value: A17 CIRB Protocol Amendment Approval: Site Addition
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A17 CIRB Protocol Amendment Approval: Site Addition

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A17 CIRB Protocol Amendment Approval: Site Addition
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Protocol amendment approval by CIRB for site addition.

PermissibleValues.value: A16  Site Issues: Competing Study
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A16  Site Issues: Competing Study

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A16  Site Issues: Competing Study
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: This refers to a local study competing for the same cohort. Should be documented as soon as staff becomes aware of it whether or not it ultimately affects any phase of accrual.

PermissibleValues.value: A15  Site Issues: Accrual Limit Reached
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A15  Site Issues: Accrual Limit Reached

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A15  Site Issues: Accrual Limit Reached
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Site no longer recruiting because their planned accrual limit was reached.  Indicate in comments whether this is considered a temporary hold because an increase in the limit is planned or if it is permanent.

PermissibleValues.value: A14  Site Issues: Local IRB/Regulatory Issues
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A14  Site Issues: Local IRB/Regulatory Issues

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A14  Site Issues: Local IRB/Regulatory Issues
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Local IRB approval delays or other regulatory issues that could delay study activity.

PermissibleValues.value: A13  Site Issues: Language/Translation Issues
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A13  Site Issues: Language/Translation Issues

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A13  Site Issues: Language/Translation Issues
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: This refers to local language barriers that could impact accrual, local language barrier with patient populations, local issues with translation of informed consent form.

PermissibleValues.value: A12  Site Issues: Accrual Limit Increased/Decreased
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A12  Site Issues: Accrual Limit Increased/Decreased

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A12  Site Issues: Accrual Limit Increased/Decreased
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Changes to the accrual limit, such as transfer of accrual spots from one site to another.

PermissibleValues.value: A11  Site Reopen
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A11  Site Reopen

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A11  Site Reopen
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: This is intended for use when specific sites reopen, usually after Accrual on Hold for study as a whole has been lifted.

PermissibleValues.value: A10  Accrual Hold Lifted
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A10  Accrual Hold Lifted

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A10  Accrual Hold Lifted
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Date accrual hold ended.

PermissibleValues.value: A8a - Accrual on Hold: protocol-defined Clinical Hold
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A8a - Accrual on Hold: protocol-defined Clinical Hold

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A8a - Accrual on Hold: protocol-defined Clinical Hold
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Accrual on hold as defined in protocol (e.g., for dose escalation/de-escalation study (e.g., for safety data review, specimen analysis, and other data evaluation procedures). Accrual Holds should be reported on the Protocol Status Update Form.

PermissibleValues.value: A8  Accrual on Hold: FDA Clinical Hold
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A8  Accrual on Hold: FDA Clinical Hold

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A8  Accrual on Hold: FDA Clinical Hold
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Study has been placed on Clinical Hold by the FDA Accrual Holds should be reported on the Protocol Status Update Form.

PermissibleValues.value: A7b  CIRB Protocol Amendment Approval: Study Burden Reduction (Visits)
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A7b  CIRB Protocol Amendment Approval: Study Burden Reduction (Visits)

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A7b  CIRB Protocol Amendment Approval: Study Burden Reduction (Visits)
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: This refers to reduction in the number of clinical visits or a change from a clinical visit to a phone contact.

PermissibleValues.value: A7a  CIRB Protocol Amendment Approval: Study Burden Reduction (Procedures)
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A7a  CIRB Protocol Amendment Approval: Study Burden Reduction (Procedures)

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A7a  CIRB Protocol Amendment Approval: Study Burden Reduction (Procedures)
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: This refers to change or removal of invasive or burdensome procedures e.g., scope, biopsy, maybe scan if it has been shown to be an accrual deterrent.

PermissibleValues.value: A6  CIRB Protocol Amendment Approval: Sample Size Change
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A6  CIRB Protocol Amendment Approval: Sample Size Change

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A6  CIRB Protocol Amendment Approval: Sample Size Change
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Change in total enrollment to planned sample size.

PermissibleValues.value: A5  CIRB Protocol Amendment Approval: Eligibility
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A5  CIRB Protocol Amendment Approval: Eligibility

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A5  CIRB Protocol Amendment Approval: Eligibility
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Protocol amendments that have a change to eligibility. Includes changes to inclusion and/or exclusion criteria, change in concomitant medications, or other eligibility factors that could impact accrual.

PermissibleValues.value: A4  Protocol Amendment Submitted to DCP
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A4  Protocol Amendment Submitted to DCP

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A4  Protocol Amendment Submitted to DCP
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Date Protocol Amendment was sent to DCP for Review This refers to all amendments that may impact accrual (usually not administrative or logistical changes) to recognize that a change to improve accrual was initiated and if possible, there should be an edit check to make sure it is followed by Protocol Amendment Approval.

PermissibleValues.value: A2  Site Issues: Drug Shipment Authorization
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A2  Site Issues: Drug Shipment Authorization

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A2  Site Issues: Drug Shipment Authorization
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: This should only be used when drug shipment to a site is authorized by CCSA  i.e., when they have received all required reg docs - (as opposed to referring to anything else about drug shipment authorization).

PermissibleValues.value: A1  Study Active
PermissibleValues.valueDescription: A1  Study Active

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A1  Study Active
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: This should be used when the study first becomes Active and only once for every study.  Study Active is determined by the study being reported as such on the Protocol Status Update Form.

PermissibleValues.value: A14a - Site Issues: Local Approval of Amendment

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A14a - Site Issues: Local Approval of Amendment
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Protocol amendment approval at the local level.

PermissibleValues.value: A18a - PI Issues: Change in PI

ValueMeaning.preferredName: A18a - PI Issues: Change in PI
ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Change in PI at a site.
